The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Friday, November 15, 2002  Martin deserves another chance 
 FROM WILLIAM TELL				 										Bangalore: The Ponnappa-ward Cape Martin, who let down a host of supporters on the opening day, deserves another chance to make amends for that failure when he takes on seven rivals for the 1,200m Hyderabad Silver Vase on Friday here. Cape Martins main rivals looks to be speedsters Days Of Glory and Bryce Canyon both stablemates, from the yard of Michael Eshwer, who are working well. However, now having had the benefit of that run, Pesi Shroff and Martin may have little difficulty is shaking of their challenge.				 										SELECTIONS				 										2.30 pm: Argentum Blue 1. Streak Of Fire 2. Nice And Noble 3.				 										3 pm: Crystal Delight 1. Auchterarder 2. Authentic Power 3.				 										3.30 pm: Imperial Legend 1. Star Cavalier 2. Brunswick 3.				 										4 pm: Cape Martin 1. Bryce Canyon 2. Days Of Glory 3.				 										4.30 pm: La Bella Vita 1. Outsmart 2. Revasser 3.				 										5 pm: Hello Baby 1. I Am Beautiful 2. Shara 3.				 										Days Best: Imperial Legend Double: Crystal Delight amp; Hello Baby
